meanings.sent1: The new pizza place outdelivers the old one in speed.

meanings.definition: To exceed in performance or quality
meanings.sent1: The new phone model outdelivers the previous one in features.
meanings.sent2: Their teamwork always outdelivers others in the company.
meanings.sent3: The student outdelivers his own expectations with his exam results.
meanings.sent4: Her creativity outdelivers any other artist in the gallery.
meanings.sent5: The sun outdelivers any artificial light with its brightness.
